Package: blockingChallenge
Type: Package
Title: Create Blocks or Strata which are Similar Within
Version: 1.0
Date: 2018-09-10
Author: Bikram Karmakar
Maintainer: Bikram Karmakar <bikramk@wharton.upenn.edu>
Description: Implements a heuristic algorithm to build blocks of a given size
	aiming to maximize similarity within strata across multiple covariates. 
	The blocking structure can be used for causal inference and for sensitivity
	analysis to unmeasured confounding. A stratified structure gives more flexibility
	for using multiple instrumental variables and direct treatment vs. control 
	analysis as evidence factors.
	Karmakar, B., Small, D. S., and Rosenbaum, P. R. (2018). 
	Rosenbaum, P. R. (2010)<ISBN:978-1-4419-1213-8>.
Enhances: optmatch
Suggests: MASS
License: MIT + file LICENSE
NeedsCompilation: no
Packaged: 2018-09-14 17:23:35 UTC; bikra
Built: R 3.6.0; ; 2018-09-14 17:37:02 UTC; windows
